---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---
<LegalLayout title="Contact" description={`Contact ${site.brand} about launch pricing, policies, security, or an invitation preview.`}>
  <Prose>
    <h2>One inbox, routed by a person</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="text-xl font-bold">{site.email}</a>.
      We respond within <strong>{site.responseWindow}</strong>, usually faster.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use this inbox for launch and pricing questions, policy requests, security reports, and
      issues from an invitation preview. Public product access and checkout are currently closed.
    </p>

    <h2>What to include</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Namescape launch or pricing question:</strong> the feature, search-pack price, or launch detail you want clarified.</li>
      <li><strong>Gateway.pink invitation-preview report:</strong> if Pinkflow invited you to a preview, include the route, request identifier, status code, and timestamp. Do not email secrets, API keys, or sensitive payloads.</li>
      <li><strong>Future purchase or billing question:</strong> the product, published price, and what you want clarified. If Pinkflow later opens checkout and you report a charge, include the transaction identifier and charge date. See the <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Privacy request:</strong> your account email, product, and the right you want to exercise. See the <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Security report:</strong> the affected company page or invitation preview, impact, reproduction steps, and a minimal proof of concept. Do not access data that is not yours.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Where we are</h2>
    <p>{site.operatorLine}. Correspondence: <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a>.</p>

    <h2>Resolution target</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to resolve launch-pricing and policy questions within
      <strong> {site.resolutionWindow}</strong> of the first message. Invitation-preview, security,
      payment, or privacy investigations may take longer; if so, we will explain what is still
      being checked.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</LegalLayout>
